<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strchr(args, '=') can read until a terminating '\0'. The function only checks args != NULL and args[0] != '\0', which does not guarantee that the object referenced by args is a properly NUL-terminated string. If args points to a buffer that is not NUL-terminated (for example a buffer of length N whose contents lack a terminating '\0', or args points to the final byte of an allocated object that is non-zero), strchr will read beyond the buffer boundary and thus violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
